    commonMistakes: ["Underestimating hours because the work feels familiar.", "Not charging for discovery or project planning.", "Forgetting review time and revision rounds.", "Leaving scope boundaries vague.", "Skipping rush fees for compressed timelines.", "Copying competitors without knowing their costs or positioning.", "Not adding margin for profit and reinvestment.", "Not writing assumptions, exclusions, and change-request rules."],
    actionableTips: ["Price from a written scope before quoting.", "Use your freelance hourly rate as an internal baseline.", "Include one or two revision rounds, then charge for additional changes.", "Add a risk buffer for ambiguity, urgency, dependencies, and technical unknowns.", "Separate direct expenses from labor assumptions.", "Write proposal assumptions clearly so the client knows what is included."],
